3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the behavior of eigenvector centrality and proposes an alternative measure based on nonbacktracking matrix, which can be relevant to data structures and algorithms for network analysis.
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the behavior of centrality measures in networks, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture for analyzing and optimizing network structures.
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes an alternative centrality measure based on nonbacktracking matrix, which can be relevant to machine learning for network analysis and prediction.
